						<!-- Enter text on the homepage here -->
						<h1>Welcome!</h1><br />
						The Terry James Resource Centre, in cooperation with the Curriculum, Special Education and Speech and Languages Divisions of the Program Department, provides students and educators with access to quality learning resources and services.<br />
<br />

             			The Centre is named for a young woman who was the Communications Officer with the former Wellington County Board of Education. Terry James held the position from 1987 until she passed away in 1993 after a lengthy struggle with cancer. As an educational communicator and a children's author, Terry was a highly respected professional and a model of courage to all who knew her.
					</td>
